claim.claim-text:
21. A method for depositing a low dielectric constant film, comprising; 
flowing a cyclic organosilicon compound and an aliphatic organosilicon compound into a reaction zone as a volume ratio of between about 1:4 and about 4:1; and 
reacting the cyclic organosilicon compound and the aliphatic organosilicon compound with an oxidizing gas while applying RF power to deposit a film having a dielectric constant of about 3 or less; 
wherein the cyclic organosilicon compound comprises at least three silicon atoms and from one to two alkyl groups bonded to each silicon atom; and 
wherein the aliphatic organosilicon compound comprises at least one silicon-hydrogen bond or at least one silicon-oxygen bond.
